==English==
===Etymology 1===
From ''[[straight]]'' + ''[[-en]]''

===Verb===
{{conj|straighten|straightens|straightened|straightened|straightening}}
# ''(transitive)'' Make [[straight]].
# ''(intransitive)'' Become straight.
# ''(transitive)'' Put in [[order]]; [[tidy up]].
# ''(transitive)'' [[Clarify]]; make a situation clear (to someone).
# ''(transitive) (slang)'' [[Bribe]]; [[corrupt]].
# ''(intransitive)'' [[Stand up]]; get up from a sitting position.

====Translations====
'''make straight'''
* Dutch: [[rechtmaken]], [[rechttrekken]], [[rechten]]

'''become straight'''
* Dutch: [[zich rechten]], [[recht]] [[worden]]

'''stand up'''
* Dutch: [[overeind]] [[springen]]; [[opspringen]]

